==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensitivity
<hw>Sen`si*tiv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being sensitive; -- used chiefly in science and the arts;
<as>as, the <ex>sensitivity</ex> of iodized silver</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sensitivity</qex> and emotivity have also been used as the
scientific term for the capacity of feeling.</q>
<rj><qau>Hickok.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensitize</ent>⟦br⟧
